<taxonomicName id="B9A3E987FA2FA436C77C1F7E34F63ECE" genus="H." lsidName="H. sphaerotheca" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="sphaerotheca">
<emphasis id="702E4C5B51B5BFD304418217C9E32F31" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">H. sphaerotheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is endemic to the Northern Territory of Australia, between the Mary River and the South Alligator River. It differs from those species in several characters that are summarised in Table 
<tableCitation id="F112658ED956B30CBDD9054F1F0047E6" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Comparison of Helicteres binhthuanensis with its morphologically closest allies (modified from Pham 1999; Phengklai 2001; Tang et al. 2007; Cowie 2011)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DDED75B0D50EFA734ADC20A6F8B0447F" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" tableUuid="DDED75B0D50EFA734ADC20A6F8B0447F">1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
